Plot the oral equivalent dose (OED) and exposure data (if applicable)

Source: R/IVIVE_outputfuncs.R
IVIVEplotting.Rd

This function plots all OEDs and any uploaded exposure data. How the OEDs are plotted is dependent upon the user-selected output type (single OED quantile or all OED samples). Exposure data (if applicable) is plotted as a point range.

Usage

IVIVEplotting(OED_data, BioactiveConc, pars, logscale, expdata)

Arguments

OED_data

A data frame of chemical names and their OEDs (either one per chemical or many per chemical if samples were returned); The first output from the IVIVEsol function

BioactiveConc

An input not used

pars

A list of all user input parameters for the entire app

logscale

Checkbox input value indicating if the user wanted the y-axis of plots to be a log10 scale

expdata

A data frame with chemical names and exposure data estimates

Value

A ggplot2 plotting object

See also

IVIVE_Plot_server(), which calls the current function, and OEDPoint_Exposure_Plot(), OEDPoint_NoExposure_Plot(), Plotdf_Prep(), OEDSample_Exposure_Plot(), OEDSample_NoExposure_Plot(), and IVIVEplot_logscale(), which are called by the current function
